EQUITABLE TRUST CO., Plaintiff-Appellee, v. William C. SCHWEBEL, Defendant-Appellant. Nos. 7558, 7645. Circuit Court of Appeals, Third Circuit. Feb. 17, 1941. Louis Sherman, of Philadelphia, Pa., for appellant. Paul Freeman, of Philadelphia, Pa. (Freeman, Fox & Steeble, of Philadelphia, Pa., and John Lloyd, Jr., of Atlantic City, N. J., on the brief), for appellee.

Before BIGGS, MARIS, and JONES, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The orders, 32 F.Supp. 241, appealed from are affirmed.
